    "In the second place, the studies delve into specific case studies and methodologies for assessing landslide vulnerability and risk (Philpott et al. 2008; Frigerio and De Amicis 2016; Arabameri and Rezaei 2019).",
    "These studies highlight the vulnerability of agricultural systems, social vulnerability assessment, and the need for a common legal framework in Europe.",
    "They provide real-world examples and techniques for evaluating and addressing landslide risks.",
    "Finally, in the third place, the studies discuss comprehensive approaches to assessing and mitigating landslide risk (van Westen et al. 2006; Pellicani et al. 2014; Peduto et al. 2017; Herrera et al. 2018).",
    "These studies introduce methods for vulnerability assessment, qualitative exposure analysis, and Bayesian modeling for prediction."
